step.context:
\text{If x packages of nuts and y packages of bolts}\\ 
\text{are being produced each day, what do we need}\\ 
\text{to maximise?}

step.reason:
\text{We need to maximise the profit from sales,}\\
\text{which may not be for the maximum number}\\
\text{of total packages produced.}

step.context:
\text{What constraints do Machines A and B impose}\\
\text{on x and y (pkgs of nuts and bolts produced}\\
\text{each day)?}

\text{For the above constraints, what does the plot }\\
\text{representing the feasible region and its corner }\\
\text{points look like?}

\text{What are the corner points and maximum}\\
\text{for objective function } T = 17.5x + 7y\\
\text{based on the graph in the previous step?}

step.reason:
\text{Since the feasible region is bounded, we can}\\
\text{establish the maximum by substituting corner} \\
\text{points in the objective function.}
